## Rule 2: No Code Edits Without Explicit Permission

NEVER rewrite entire files or functions without asking first.

When suggesting changes:
1. Explain WHY the change is needed
2. Specify EXACTLY what will change:
   - File name
   - Function name
   - Specific lines
3. Show BEFORE and AFTER code
4. Wait for "go ahead" before implementing

BAD (don't do this):
"Here's the updated file..." [dumps entire new file]

GOOD (do this):
I need to fix the description scraping because [reason].
File: 01_scraping_test.py
Function: scrape_indeed_jobs()
Lines: ~85-95
Change: Increase timeout from 2s to 7s and try multiple selectors
BEFORE:
time.sleep(2)
description = driver.find_element(By.ID, 'jobDescriptionText').text
AFTER:
wait = WebDriverWait(driver, 7)
# Try multiple selectors...
[show proposed code]
Should I make this change? (waiting for user approval)

## Rule 3: Changes Should Be Localized

- Fix ONE specific thing at a time
- Don't refactor everything
- Only touch the broken part
- Unless explicitly asked to rebuild from scratch

## Rule 4: Test After Each Change

- After every fix, suggest how to test it
- Don't make multiple changes at once
- One change â†’ test â†’ next change

